refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringxdiff_string_patch stringstr stringpatch intflags stringerror
Patches a string with a unified patch string.

  &reftitle.examples;



    xdiff_string_patch example


     The following code applies changes to some article.



<?php
$old_article = file_get_contents('./old_article.txt');
$diff = $_SERVER['patch']; /* Let's say that someone pasted a patch to html form */

$errors = '';

$new_article = xdiff_string_patch($old_article, $diff, XDIFF_PATCH_NORMAL, $errors);
if (is_string($new_article)) {
    echo "New article:\n";
    echo $new_article;
}

if (strlen($errors)) {
    echo "Rejects: \n";
    echo $errors;
}

?>
